t  cycling weekly skip to content » rfigt cycling weekly subscribe now digital edition cycling weekly george hincapie’s scott addict cycling weekly april   shares shares george hincapie has been riding shimanos electronic di this year but for the tough classics hes switching back to the mechanical dura ace  all is not well in the shimano camp and a complete swap to the  group is avoided with the older  rear mech the columbia mechanics feel the older cage design gives more security in preventing the chain dropping off the jockey wheels  makes another appearance with the cranks as these are the only shimano cranks able to accept the wireless srm a rear mounted wireless speed sensor keeps as much as possible out of the wind roughly taped to the rear rim is the wheel magnet not pretty but if it works another change for hincapie is a switch from his addict frame with integrated post to the nonintegrated version presumably for ease of saddle height adjustment and perhaps a little extra comfort continental pro edition competition mm tyres give the extra grip and comfort that are needed for the rough cobbles interestingly hincapie chose to run his hed carbonlite  carbon wheels over the cobbles for flanders and roubaix although his mechanics prepared fir st rims on dura ace hubs just in case hincapie is one of the few riders who rides with full deep section rims for the cobbled classics old  dura ace rear mech magnets taped onto rear rim and it’s last year’s rear mech at the back of the bike too wireless rear mounted speed sensor follow cycling weekly on twitter related links heinrich haussler’s cervelo s fabian cancellara’s specialized tarmac sl cancellara derailed by broken chain devolder wins tour of flanders for second time vittoria corsa g isotech c folding road tyre  oe evans cycles £ save  buy now flr f race road cycling shoes    white merlin cycles £ save  buy now seesense icon rear light chain reaction cycles £ save  buy now most read this week ‘my legs look tired’ 